{"timestamp":"2026-06-01T10:02:17Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","id":"ctc_07cddc99d8d2faba016a454938f57c8191ac87c771ac7a4e58","status":"completed","call_id":"call_wYI5hUGHvXed0ZvxQ0fI5UVF","name":"apply_patch","input":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: docs/demo-short.md\n+# Codex Capability Demo\n+\n+Codex is a coding partner that can move from intent to verified change inside a real repo. It reads the project, respects existing patterns, edits files directly, and runs the same checks an engineer would use before calling work done.\n+\n+In a typical session, Codex can split work across focused sub-agents, inspect independent parts of the codebase in parallel, then fold the findings back into one implementation. That makes it useful for tasks that need both breadth and precision: tracing a bug through backend tests, updating a React view, checking docs, and verifying the final behavior.\n+\n+The core loop is practical:\n+\n+1. Understand the repo and the user's goal.\n+2. Make the smallest coherent code or documentation change.\n+3. Run targeted verification.\n+4. Report exactly what changed, what passed, and what remains risky.\n+\n+This demo artifact was created through that loop: repo context first, scoped design second, direct file edit third, and verification last.\n*** End Patch\n"}}
{"timestamp":"2026-06-01T10:02:19Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"patch_apply_end","call_id":"call_wYI5hUGHvXed0ZvxQ0fI5UVF","turn_id":"019f1ea5-b5ba-7842-b68c-1123b13b313b","stdout":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA docs/demo-short.md\n","stderr":"","success":true,"changes":{"/workspace/cot/docs/demo-short.md":{"type":"add","content":"# Codex Capability Demo\n\nCodex is a coding partner that can move from intent to verified change inside a real repo. It reads the project, respects existing patterns, edits files directly, and runs the same checks an engineer would use before calling work done.\n\nIn a typical session, Codex can split work across focused sub-agents, inspect independent parts of the codebase in parallel, then fold the findings back into one implementation. That makes it useful for tasks that need both breadth and precision: tracing a bug through backend tests, updating a React view, checking docs, and verifying the final behavior.\n\nThe core loop is practical:\n\n1. Understand the repo and the user's goal.\n2. Make the smallest coherent code or documentation change.\n3. Run targeted verification.\n4. Report exactly what changed, what passed, and what remains risky.\n\nThis demo artifact was created through that loop: repo context first, scoped design second, direct file edit third, and verification last.\n"}},"status":"completed"}}
